This paper deals with device-to-device (D2D) communication in cellular networks, which is a subfield of networked systems and technologies. Specifically, it focuses on caching placement in D2D-enabled networks, which involves optimization and auction theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory and optimization techniques, which are common in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper deals with content caching, which is a topic in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
